title: For Sale/Trade:  Arisaka Type 38
postcontent: Up for consideration is a piece of history from WW2.  It is a Japanese Arisaka type 38 rifle chambered in 6.5 mm. This rifle was made in 1939 at the Koishikawa Arsenal in Japan. It is a Pacific Theatre battlefield captured rifle. This is fact. The rifle has a chrysanthemum symbol on the barrel breach that indicates that rifle belonged to the emperor as did all Japanese arms. All rifles surrendered by captured soldiers were defaced on this symbol. It was their way of not letting the emporers symbol be captured. This rifle is intact and was picked up off battlefield or from deceased soldier. Its rare and adds a premium to these rifles. This rifles bolt, breach, receiver, and barrel are in working order and can be shot. They are extremely aqccurate. It has never been shot since bring back from WW2. When cleaning, I took the butstock plate loose and sand fell out! I have it and will be included. It has original cleaning rod and all numbers matching gun. I knew the man that owned this rifle. His grandson sold it to me after his passing 5 years ago. The stock is not cracked. They were made in 2 pieces and dovetailed together from cherry wood. Has cool battle scars/dings in Stock. Overall very clean and in guarenteed working condition. You could be the first to shoot this weapon from the war. It is 80 years old this year. I have researched this rifle for weeks and will provide all research papers with it and sources. Here's your chance to own a historical rifle from the Axis side. All questions welcomed at my e-mail address.   Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Pre ban Knights Armament SR-25 Match Rifle
postcontent: Looking to sell my pre ban Knights Armament SR-25 Target model .308 Semi auto rifle. Rarely used safe queen. I’m asking $6,000 OBO. Email me for pictures, questions, or if you’d like to see it. Cash or certified check only. Below is a description of the rifle and its history. Knight's Armament Company SR-25 Match Rifle, chambered in 7.62NATO. This rifle was manufactured before the '94 ban. This rifle has been fired less than 200 rounds. It is everything you want it to be. The SR-25 (Stoner Rifle-25) is a designated marksman rifle designed by Eugene Stoner and manufactured by Knight's Armament Company. The SR-25 uses a rotating bolt and a direct impingement gas system. It is loosely based on Stoner's AR-10, rebuilt in its original 7.62×51mm NATO caliber. Up to 60% of parts of the SR-25 are interchangeable with the AR-15 and M16—everything but the upper and lower receivers, the hammer, the barrel assembly and the bolt carrier group. SR-25 barrels were originally manufactured by Remington Arms with its 5R (5 grooves, right twist) rifling, with twist 1:11.25 (1 complete turn in 11.25 inches or 286 millimetres). The heavy 24 in (610 mm) barrel is free-floating, so handguards are attached to the front of the receiver and do not touch the barrel. First military purchase was spearheaded by the U.S. Navy in the early 1990s; the first operational deployment and use of the SR-25 sniper rifle was with U.S. Navy SEAL snipers supporting operations in Somalia in 1993. The rifle is 100% original parts. Item is used but in excellent condition.

title: For Sale:  Colt 1911 Mark IV Series 80 Customized!
postcontent:
I’ve customized this and tuned it for combat shooting, but I’m getting old and I’m just not competing anymore. Looking for a buyer who will love this firearm like I have. If it means anything, this was my personal firearm that traveled with me through out my military career. It has been to various posts both domestic and abroad. Go Army!
MORE PHOTOS HERE: https://photos.app.goo.gl/G9bBvxThPTRUbWaE3It includes:
2 BARRELS: (1) Heinie 45 ACP Drop In Compensator with 5.5” Stainless Steel Barrel and Bushing. (2) 5” Barrel with custom fitted bushing and polished throat.
+ Extended magazine release+ Extended ambidextrous safety+ Light-weight trigger+ Wilson Combat matching hammer and sear+ Wilson Combat "Group-Gripper" (google it!)+ Beavertail+ Beveled magazine well w/ flat mainspring housing+ Checkered front strap+ Checkered trigger guard+ Adjustable sights with FAT front sight+ Flared ejection port+ Front serrations+ Brand new Cerakote+ Some original parts (for parts that were replaced). If there in the “parts” picture, they are yours with the sale.+ SUPER CRISP trigger** It’s not a "light" trigger (it’s about 5 lbs), it’s just that the trigger has virtually ZERO play before or after hammer activation. Combined with the Wilson matching hammer/sear, this is my most prized customization. Pulling the trigger is like breaking a thin rod of glass. When the trigger moves the hammer falls; and when the hammer falls the trigger stops moving. Reset is tactile and audible. Must feel!
AS IS:
The magazine well is scratched from use on the underside. See pictures.
Be warned: I have removed the Series 80 drop safety mechanism. This interfered with how I wanted to tune the trigger. I still have the plunger, but the upper and lower sear levers are gone. You can replace these for a few bucks and get the safety working again if you wanted…but definitely not worth the sacrifice in the trigger feel, IMHO. Up to you, of course, if you buy.
The rear sight adjustment screw gets loose sometimes. Seems to be holding in there for now, but it has come loose before.
There, of course, may be other issues I’m not aware of, and I take no responsibility for issues not listed here. Gun is sold “as is.”
